ce:section.ce:para:
The effect of the presence of P-CQDs on the P3HT:PCBM active layer morphology was examined by performing AFM analysis and the images taken were given in Fig. 2
                     . The average roughness (Ra) and grain size distribution results were used to confirm the incorporation and positive effect of P-CQDs (Table 1
                     ). The P3HT:PCBM layer prepared with the addition of 1 vol% of P-CQDs (8.90 nm) and 3 vol% of P-CQDs (6.28 nm) with lower Ra values exhibited smoother surfaces in comparison to the bare P3HT:PCBM layer (15.49 nm) and showed more homogeneous film morphology, leading to efficient hole carrier transfer through the films [26]. This indicates that the lower amount of P-CQDs can well mix with the bulk solution. With the increasing concentration of P-CQDs addition, the Ra values increased due to the agglomeration on the thin films, making surfaces rougher and disordered. Since increased P-CQDs additive in P3HT:PCBM solution resulted increased volume of solvent, during spin coating, fast evaporation of the solvent caused to form agglomerated particles leaving bunched small areas of P-CQDs on the photoactive layer [27]. It should be noted that the excessive concentration of P-CQDs may present a negative effect on the charge separation and transfer properties.
